name: Batch Compressed Scordite II-Grade
description: Condensed scordite, the II-Grade cousin of normal scordite, has a 5% better yield. The increase may seem insignificant, but matters greatly to new miners where every ISK counts. Scordite is amongst the most common ore types in the central regions of known universe. It has a fair bit of Tritanium and Pyerite. Good choice for those starting their mining careers. This material was compressed using an older process that compressed batches of raw materials into units using a set input quantity. Newer compression technology uses a more flexible one-to-one unit compression system.
